President Obama will be awarding National Medals of Science and National Medals of Technology and Innovation to 17 scientists, engineers, mathematicians, and innovators on Friday, January 22. The Medal of Science recognizes outstanding contributions to science, engineering, and mathematics, while the Medal of Technology and Innovation recognizes lasting contributions to America's competitiveness and quality of life. The event will be open press, but space is limited, and media members must RSVP by January 21. Access to the White House complex requires filling out a form by the deadline. Confirmation and further instructions will be sent to approved media attendees.